{#- Changelog — tabular rendering.

    One row per version; most recent first. Inline delta cells use the
    `+A / ~C / -R` shorthand (added / changed / resolved). A detail block
    immediately below the table enumerates T-IDs for the latest entry
    (capped at `_max`) so the most recent run is easy to audit without
    scrolling the table horizontally.

    Data shape per entry (see schemas/threat-model.output.schema.yaml):
      version, date, mode, baseline_sha, current_sha
      changed_files, changed_lines ({insertions, deletions})
      added:    { threats: [T-NNN,...], components: [C-NN,...], attack_surface: [E-NN,...] }
      changed:  { threats: [T-NNN,...], notes_by_id: { T-NNN: "..." } }
      resolved: { threats: [T-NNN,...], reason_by_id: { T-NNN: "..." } }
      reanalyzed_components, carried_forward_components, note
-#}
{%- set _max = 10 -%}
## Changelog

_Append-only history of assessment runs. Most recent first._

| Version | Date | Mode | Depth | Reasoning | Baseline → Current | Δ Threats | Code | Note |
|---------|------|------|-------|-----------|--------------------|-----------|------|------|
{% for entry in changelog %}
{%- set v             = entry.version -%}
{%- set date          = entry.date or '—' -%}
{%- set mode          = (entry.mode or 'full') | lower -%}
{%- set depth         = (entry.assessment_depth or '—') | lower -%}
{%- set reasoning     = entry.reasoning_model or '—' -%}
{%- set baseline_sha  = entry.baseline_sha or '' -%}
{%- set current_sha   = entry.current_sha or '' -%}
{%- set has_baseline  = (baseline_sha | length) > 0 -%}
{%- set short_base    = baseline_sha[:7] -%}
{%- set short_cur     = current_sha[:7] if current_sha else '—' -%}
{%- set added_t       = (entry.added.threats   if entry.added   else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set changed_t     = (entry.changed.threats if entry.changed else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set resolved_t    = (entry.resolved.threats if entry.resolved else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set changed_files = entry.changed_files | default(none) -%}
{%- set cl            = entry.changed_lines or {} -%}
{%- set ins           = cl.insertions | default(none) -%}
{%- set dels          = cl.deletions | default(none) -%}
{%- set note          = (entry.note or '') | trim -%}
{#- Aggressive truncation — the table row is narrow; long notes wrap the
    whole changelog illegibly. Upstream the orchestrator is instructed to
    keep `note` ≤12 words. -#}
{%- if note|length > 60 -%}{%- set note = note[:58] ~ '…' -%}{%- endif -%}
{%- if note -%}{%- set note = note | replace('|', '\\|') -%}{%- endif -%}
{%- set delta_cell = '+' ~ (added_t|length) ~ ' / ~' ~ (changed_t|length) ~ ' / -' ~ (resolved_t|length) -%}
{%- if has_baseline -%}
{%- set sha_cell = '`' ~ short_base ~ '` → `' ~ short_cur ~ '`' -%}
{%- elif v == 1 and mode == 'full' -%}
{%- set sha_cell = '_(initial)_' -%}
{%- else -%}
{%- set sha_cell = '—' -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- set code_parts = [] -%}
{%- if changed_files is not none and changed_files -%}
{%- set _ = code_parts.append((changed_files|string) ~ ' files') -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- if ins is not none and dels is not none -%}
{%- set _ = code_parts.append('+' ~ ins ~ '/-' ~ dels) -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- set code_cell = code_parts | join(', ') if code_parts else '—' -%}
| v{{ v }} | {{ date }} | {{ mode }} | {{ depth }} | {{ reasoning }} | {{ sha_cell }} | {{ delta_cell }} | {{ code_cell }} | {{ note or '—' }} |
{% endfor %}
{#- Detail block for the LATEST changelog entry. Capped at `_detail_max`
    T-IDs per bucket (Added / Changed / Resolved) with a `+N more` suffix.
    Matches the per-version detail layout in the bulleted template and
    the `_sample_ids` cap in render_completion_summary.py.

    The block only renders when at least one bucket has entries — otherwise
    the table alone is sufficient. -#}
{%- set _detail_max = 5 -%}
{%- if changelog -%}
{%- set latest = changelog[0] -%}
{%- set la_t   = (latest.added.threats     if latest.added    else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set lc_t   = (latest.changed.threats   if latest.changed  else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set lr_t   = (latest.resolved.threats  if latest.resolved else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- if la_t or lc_t or lr_t %}

**Latest run (v{{ latest.version }}) — threat-level detail:**

{% if la_t -%}
- **Added ({{ la_t|length }}):** {% for tid in la_t[:_detail_max] %}[{{ tid }}](#{{ tid|lower }}){% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}{% if (la_t|length) > _detail_max %}, +{{ (la_t|length) - _detail_max }} more{% endif %}
{% endif -%}
{% if lc_t -%}
- **Changed ({{ lc_t|length }}):** {% for tid in lc_t[:_detail_max] %}[{{ tid }}](#{{ tid|lower }}){% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}{% if (lc_t|length) > _detail_max %}, +{{ (lc_t|length) - _detail_max }} more{% endif %}
{% endif -%}
{% if lr_t -%}
- **Resolved ({{ lr_t|length }}):** {% for tid in lr_t[:_detail_max] %}[{{ tid }}](#{{ tid|lower }}){% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}{% if (lr_t|length) > _detail_max %}, +{{ (lr_t|length) - _detail_max }} more{% endif %}
{% endif -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- endif -%}
